  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to see all messages sent when I open the application, even when they were sent when Status desktop app was closed.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n*Summary*: messages sent while status-desktop app is not running are lost\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nno lost messages\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nmessages are lost\r\n![offl](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/39933937-fa64ba5a-554c-11e8-8ac7-af87dddbe6e8.png)\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n*Requirements*: 1-1 chat; user A is using status-mobile, User B is using status-desktop\r\n \r\n- Open StatusIm as User B\r\n- add User A\r\n- send several messages from user A to user B and vi—Åe versa\r\n- quit status-desktop\r\n- send several messages from user A (from status-mobile app)\r\n- open status-desktop\r\n- check chat with User A\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: StatusIm desktop (version 2018-05-07)\r\n* Operating System: MacOS High Sierra 10.13.4, Ubuntu 18.04\r\n**NOTE:** vice versa scenario is working fine, so if you send a message from the desktop app when mobile app will be closed -  everything will appear when you open the mobile app",
